Seriously f$&) the last Jedi, on that note this movie did what it had to do and saved Star Wars. The actors crushed it throughout the whole movie. The energy and enthusiasm they brought sold this movie. The last hour of the movie is some of the best Star Wars ever. C3PO finally getting some love!

This movie doesn't deserve a 1. It certainly doesn't deserve a 10, or even an 8. Inconsistent pacing, an incomprehensible plot, and lack of internal consistency even among the 3 sequel trilogy films hamper this final installment, which fails to ask any important questions, or provide any meaningful answers. It actually reverses some of the most important parts of the prequel and original trilogies, and fails to capture the imagination. The Skywalker Saga was over before this movie was even conceptualized.

It just felt like everyone making the movie was tired of Star Wars and just wanted to end it as fast as possible- so they just did the easiest ending they could think of. If they did an episode 10, 11, & 12- you could just skip 7, 8, & 9 and you wouldn't really miss anything -nothing happens in this movie that hasn't already happened in Star Wars before.
Felt like someone wrote a bad fan fiction. It didn't flow, and some parts were downright cringe and awful.
I love the movie best Star Wars ending love it

A movie for true star wars fans, if you can keep an open mind going into this movie and enter with a blank slate then you will be very pleasantly surprised at how JJ Abram pulls off this wonderful close to the skywalker saga.
it feel like they crammed two movies into one. very nostalgic but I would have liked it if it was more subtle.

JJ had a mess to clean up. He did an admirable job. The movie was slow in the beginning, fun in the middle, and excellent in the end. The final sequence of scenes really brings the trilogy and the whole 9 movie arc to a solid conclusion.
